%N A388041 a(n) = n! * ((n-2) * 2^(n-1) + 1).
%C A388041 Number of ways to sit n people on linearly ordered benches and choose 2 people from any bench.
%C A388041 If the benches are not linearly ordered the sequence is A386961.
%C A388041 If only 1 bench is used the sequence is A001804.
%F A388041 a(n) = n! * A000337(n-1), n > 0.
%F A388041 E.g.f.: x^2 / ((1-x) * (1-2*x)^2).
%e A388041 a(5)=5880 since the number of ways are (number of people in parentheses, configurations with linearly ordered benches):
%e A388041   1 bench (5): 120 configurations, 1200 ways;
%e A388041   2 benches (4,1): 240 configurations, 1440 ways;
%e A388041   2 benches (3,2): 240 configurations, 960 ways;
%e A388041   3 benches (3,1,1): 360 configurations, 1080 ways;
%e A388041   3 benches (2,2,1): 360 configurations, 720 ways;
%e A388041   4 benches (2,1,1,1): 480 configurations, 480 ways;
%e A388041   5 benches (1,1,1,1,1): 120 configurations, 0 ways, for a total of 5880 ways.
